{
  "texts": [
    "Multimodal approaches have demonstrated the potential to outperform single-modality models, signifying its promising future.",
    "The synthesis of data from diverse sources, such as histopathology images and genomic sequences, offers a more comprehensive view of the disease, potentially leading to more accurate and clinically actionable insights.",
    "In conclusion, the dynamic evolution of DL in medical research, particularly in histopathology and genomics, underlines its potential in fostering breakthroughs in our understanding of diagnosis and treatment of cancer.",
    "Nevertheless, a considerable scope for further exploration and advancement remains.",
    "As the fields continue to grow and technology continues to improve, we expect that DL will play an increasing role in shaping the landscape of precision medicine.Fig. 11Fig."
  ]
